
"I'm Debra. " I looked up to him, hugging my book to my chest.
"Not only do you have a pretty voice, but you also have a pretty name to match it!"
The blush on my face grew darker and I smiled more.
"Is your song finished yet?"Pit asked glancing to my book then back to my face.
"Nope...I just started working on it today."I sat back down next to the tree.
"Can I hear it?"The angel sat next to me, giving a big smile.
"I guess so."I nodded, opening up the book
Pit leaned back on the tree, waiting for me to start singing.
I  cleared my throat, and started reading the words on the paper, then I started to sing them."If you ever find yourself stuck in the middle of the sea, I'll sail the world to find you~" I paused, flipping the page over."If you find yourself lost in the dark and you can't see, I'll be the light to guide you~"Another momentary pause, but this time it wasn't to flip the page."Find out what we're of, when we are called to help our friends in need~...you can count on me like one, two, three..."
When I stopped, Pit looked back to me,"I like it, that song is worth finishing. "